    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-16T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-16T23:00:00-05:00" n="225"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">892.248/46: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-17T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >July 17, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>350. My telegram No. 306, June 12, 5 p.m.<note n="95" xml:id="d225fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> In view of the enormous amount of unfavorable publicity in
                    the Thai press over a period of many months regarding the stopping of the war
                    planes purchased by Thailand, I recommend that the Department inform me by
                    telegraph immediately upon the settlement of the claim in order that favorable
                    counteracting publicity may be secured here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
